commit.message: Updated Changelog for 3.2 release.
Makefile bug fix for cross-compiling. Also includes doc fix.

Update ebfc to generate 64-bit ELF files (instead of 32-bit).

In addition to updating the code for 64-bit targets, the source has
been generally cleaned up, and some minor improvements have been made
to the elfparts API. Comments and documentation have been likewise
improved.
Fixes for various crashes on malformed ELF files.
updated to current GPLv2 text.
Fix makenumberfmts() to check for absent tables.
Fix missing check for end of string.
Allow infection of any file type with an e_entry value.
Fixed check for too-large jump.
More error checking for strange/malformed ELF files to avoid segfaults.
Note for release 3.1a.
Bug fix: look out for macros that are shorter than prefixes.
Explicitly set data field to NULL!
Tweak lszr change to use consistent names and comments.

Merge pull request #5 from lszr/master

commit.message:
Allow full hexadecimal output

Sometime, you don't want to have character but only hexadecimal, even in data
section.

Use new function elfrw_count_Dyns().

This addresses issue #4, again. Hopefully for real this time.

This replaces the previous check-in, which failed to solve the actual
problem, and should not have seen the light of day. Sigh.

Add functions to load some struct arrays by byte size instead of by count.
